{"type":"message","id":"65ff6c6b","parentId":"f755f17c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T04:17:33.190Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to compare the current state against the last known state from heartbeat-state.json.\n\n**Last known state (heartbeat-state.json):**\n- Active sessions: `ed2d0b5d`, `6f3323ef`, `e7885813`\n- Idle sessions: `-5163901258`, `telegram:direct:6053576134`\n- Failed sessions: `-5168104492`\n- Orphaned crons: `ac986a8d`, `b653a6c0`\n- Last report: 2026-04-15T04:12:00Z\n\n**Current state (sessions_list at 04:16 UTC):**\n\n\nLooking at what's actually running now, I see the cron jobs are mostly the same—`ed2d0b5d`, `6f3323ef`, and `e7885813` are all still active. But there's been a shift in the background sessions: the main session has finished and the QLHV group session is now done too, while the direct telegram channel remains idle. The orphaned cron jobs haven't changed, so the main differences are just these session state transitions.\n\nI'm also noticing a few new active subagents spawned from the cron:ed2d0b5d session—`ba49ac6d` and `c2d275a5`—which weren't running before. And there's a new message from the lead asking about the setup package not being visible to users, which is the current priority I need to address. I've identified the key changes since the last heartbeat: the main session ended, there are new subagents spawned from the 5p monitor running, and the DTLX group session completed its work. These are real state changes worth reporting, so I'll compose and send the report.","thinkingSignature":"307c5e09d6d994da6f73325a51e337ea479846ad352dd3e7b13c7584f832c9f5"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state against `heartbeat-state.json` (captured at 04:12 UTC):\n\n**Changes detected:**\n- ✅ Main session (`agent:master-orchestrator:main`) ended normally at 04:13 UTC — was not in prior active list\n- ✅ DTLX Ecosystem group (`-5168104492`) — session completed normally at 02:55 UTC, now